  "body": "This seems so basic that I can't believe I didn't find it in first 5 seconds of google search (let alone 20 minutes) :joy: \r\n\r\nAnyways, I'm using `remix-ide` locally and I want to access **and save** my local files.\r\nI can load my local files into IDE but then they are on the `browser` file system and no changes are saved locally.\r\n\r\nThere is this magic command in the docs:\r\n```\r\nremixd -s <absolute-path-to-the-shared-folder> --remix-ide https://remix.ethereum.org\r\n```\r\nBut when I try to do something like this it doesn't work:\r\n```\r\nremixd -s <absolute-path-to-the-shared-folder> --remix-ide http://localhost:8080\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe issue seems so basic to me - like didn't anyone ever think it would be cool to use **everything** locally?\r\n(maybe this is a dummy question but I decided to go with it) :joy: \r\n\r\nEDIT:\r\nAlmost forgot... this is the error:\r\n```\r\nError: listen EADDRINUSE: address already in use 127.0.0.1:65520\r\n```",
